# Architecture Issues and Debugging Approach

## Current Traffic Flow

User
→ CloudFront + AWS WAF
→ ALB Ingress
→ EKS Pods
→ Aurora PostgreSQL / S3 / SNS / SQS / Lambda / SES

Note: We are not using NLB. We are using ALB Ingress with target-type IP, so ALB directly registers Pod IPs in the target group.

---

## 1. Frontend / CloudFront Issue

### Issue

Frontend page is not loading or old frontend content is showing.

### Possible Reasons

- CloudFront cache issue
- S3 origin issue
- Latest React build not uploaded properly
- WAF blocking the request
- DNS issue
- S3 bucket policy or OAC issue
- CloudFront invalidation not done after deployment

### Debugging Approach

First, I check whether the domain is resolving correctly and whether the request is reaching CloudFront.

I check:

- Route 53 DNS record
- CloudFront distribution status
- CloudFront origin configuration
- CloudFront cache behavior
- S3 bucket objects
- S3 bucket policy or OAC configuration
- WAF sampled requests
- CloudFront invalidation status

Commands:

    curl -I https://app-domain.com
    curl -v https://app-domain.com

### Interview Answer

If the frontend is not loading, I first check the browser network tab or use curl to see the CloudFront response. Then I verify CloudFront origin, cache behavior, S3 objects, WAF logs, and DNS. If old content is showing, I check whether CloudFront invalidation was done after the latest deployment.

