## 3. CloudFront API Routing Issue

### Issue

Frontend loads, but backend API calls fail.

### Possible Reasons

- /api/* behavior missing in CloudFront
- API traffic routed to S3 instead of ALB
- ALB origin misconfigured
- Required HTTP methods not allowed
- Headers or cookies not forwarded properly
- CORS issue
- WAF blocking API request
- ALB target group unhealthy

### Debugging Approach

I check:

- CloudFront behavior for /api/*
- Whether /api/* is mapped to ALB origin
- Allowed HTTP methods like GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, OPTIONS
- Header forwarding
- CORS response headers
- WAF logs
- ALB target group health

Commands:

    curl -I https://app-domain.com/api/health
    curl -v https://app-domain.com/api/health

### Interview Answer

If the frontend loads but API calls fail, I check CloudFront path-based routing first. Static frontend requests should go to S3, and API requests like /api/* should go to ALB. Then I verify ALB target health, CORS, and whether CloudFront is forwarding required headers and methods.

