## 4. ALB / Ingress Issue

### Issue

ALB is not getting created from Kubernetes Ingress.

### Possible Reasons

- AWS Load Balancer Controller is not running
- Incorrect Ingress annotations
- Missing or wrong IngressClass
- IAM permission issue with ALB controller role
- Public/private subnet tags are missing
- Security group creation permission issue

### Debugging Approach

I check:

- Kubernetes Ingress events
- AWS Load Balancer Controller logs
- Ingress annotations
- IngressClass
- IAM role permissions of ALB controller
- Subnet tags

Important subnet tags:

    kubernetes.io/cluster/<cluster-name> = shared or owned
    kubernetes.io/role/elb = 1
    kubernetes.io/role/internal-elb = 1

Commands:

    kubectl get ingress -n <namespace>
    kubectl describe ingress <ingress-name> -n <namespace>
    kubectl get pods -n kube-system | grep aws-load-balancer
    kubectl logs -n kube-system deployment/aws-load-balancer-controller

### Interview Answer

If ALB is not created, I check Ingress describe output and AWS Load Balancer Controller logs. Common causes are missing subnet tags, wrong annotations, wrong IngressClass, or IAM permission issues with the controller role.

