## 9. ImagePullBackOff Issue

### Issue

Pod cannot pull image from ECR.

### Possible Reasons

- Wrong image tag
- Image not present in ECR
- Wrong ECR repository URL
- IAM permission issue
- ECR/network connectivity issue
- Image deleted by ECR lifecycle policy

### Debugging Approach

I check:

- Image URI
- Image tag in ECR
- ECR repository
- Node IAM permission
- ECR connectivity
- Pod events

Commands:

    kubectl describe pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>
    aws ecr describe-images --repository-name <repo-name>

### Interview Answer

If pod shows ImagePullBackOff, I verify whether the image tag exists in ECR, whether the image URI is correct, and whether worker nodes have permission and connectivity to pull the image.

