## 10. Database Connectivity Issue

### Issue

Backend cannot connect to Aurora PostgreSQL.

### Possible Reasons

- Wrong DB endpoint
- Wrong credentials
- Security group issue
- Aurora cluster unavailable
- DB is in private subnet and not reachable from EKS
- DNS issue
- Max DB connections reached
- Connection pool issue

### Debugging Approach

I check:

- Backend pod logs
- Aurora cluster status
- DB writer endpoint
- DB credentials
- Security groups
- Route tables / NACL
- DB connection count
- Connectivity from pod to DB on port 5432

Commands:

    kubectl logs <backend-pod> -n <namespace>
    kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -n <namespace> -- sh
    nslookup <aurora-endpoint>
    nc -zv <aurora-endpoint> 5432

### Interview Answer

If backend cannot connect to Aurora, I check application logs, DB endpoint, credentials, security groups, and network connectivity from the pod. Since Aurora is private, only backend/EKS security group should be allowed on PostgreSQL port 5432.

