## 11. Aurora Performance Issue

### Issue

Application is slow because of database performance.

### Possible Reasons

- High DB connections
- Slow queries
- Missing indexes
- Locking/blocking queries
- CPU or ACU scaling pressure
- Connection pool misconfiguration
- Long-running transactions

### Debugging Approach

I check:

- CloudWatch DB metrics
- Aurora Performance Insights
- CPU / ACU usage
- DB connections
- Deadlocks
- Slow queries
- Application timeout logs

### Interview Answer

If database latency is suspected, I check Aurora CloudWatch metrics and Performance Insights. I look for high connections, slow queries, blocking sessions, CPU/ACU pressure, deadlocks, and application timeout errors.

