## 15. SES Issue

### Issue

SES is not sending emails.

### Possible Reasons

- Email/domain identity not verified
- SES account is in sandbox
- Recipient not verified in sandbox mode
- Sending quota exceeded
- Lambda role does not have SES permission
- Email rejected due to policy/content
- DKIM/SPF records not configured properly

### Debugging Approach

I check:

- SES verified identities
- SES sandbox status
- SES sending quota
- SES bounce/complaint metrics
- Lambda logs
- IAM permission for ses:SendEmail or ses:SendRawEmail
- DKIM/SPF records

### Interview Answer

If SES email is not received, I check whether SES domain or email identity is verified, whether the account is still in sandbox, and whether sending quota is available. I also check Lambda logs and IAM permissions.

