## 16. Deployment / Rollout Issue

### Issue

New deployment failed.

### Possible Reasons

- Wrong image tag
- New application bug
- ConfigMap/Secret issue
- Readiness probe failing
- DB migration issue
- Resource limit issue
- Application startup issue

### Debugging Approach

I check:

- Deployment rollout status
- ReplicaSets
- Pod events
- Pod logs
- Readiness probe
- Image tag
- ConfigMap/Secret changes

Commands:

    kubectl rollout status deployment/<deployment-name> -n <namespace>
    kubectl describe deployment <deployment-name> -n <namespace>
    kubectl get rs -n <namespace>
    kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
    kubectl logs <pod-name> -n <namespace>

Rollback command:

    kubectl rollout undo deployment/<deployment-name> -n <namespace>

### Interview Answer

If deployment fails, I check rollout status, ReplicaSet, pod events, and pod logs. If the issue impacts users, I rollback to the previous stable version using Kubernetes rollout undo.

