## 17. CloudWatch / Logging Issue

### Issue

Application issue happened, but logs are missing in CloudWatch.

### Possible Reasons

- Application is not writing logs to stdout/stderr
- Fluent Bit / CloudWatch agent issue
- IAM permission missing
- Wrong log group or log stream
- Log retention/filtering issue

### Debugging Approach

I check:

- Pod logs using kubectl
- CloudWatch log group
- Log agent pods
- IAM permissions
- Fluent Bit or CloudWatch agent configuration
- Application logging configuration

Commands:

    kubectl logs <pod-name> -n <namespace>
    kubectl get pods -n amazon-cloudwatch
    kubectl logs <cloudwatch-agent-pod> -n amazon-cloudwatch

### Interview Answer

If logs are missing in CloudWatch, I first check pod logs using kubectl. If logs exist in Kubernetes but not in CloudWatch, I check the log agent, IAM permissions, log group configuration, and whether the application is logging to stdout/stderr.

